<BaseLayout
  title="Important Disclosures | Canyon Strategic Wealth"
  description="Regulatory information and important notices for clients and prospective clients of Canyon Strategic Wealth, a Registered Investment Adviser."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Important Disclosures</h1>
    <p>Regulatory information and important notices for our clients and prospective clients.</p>
  </div>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="compliance-content">
      <h3>Registered Investment Adviser</h3>
      <p>
        Canyon Strategic Wealth, LLC is a Registered Investment Adviser. Registration with the SEC
        or any state securities authority does not imply a certain level of skill or training.
        Additional information about Canyon Strategic Wealth, including its advisory services, fees,
        and business practices, is available through the Investment Adviser Public Disclosure
        (IAPD) database at
        <a href="https://adviserinfo.sec.gov/firm/summary/325175" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >adviserinfo.sec.gov</a
        >.
      </p>

      <h3>Fiduciary Duty</h3>
      <p>
        As a registered investment adviser, Canyon Strategic Wealth has a fiduciary duty to act in
        the best interest of our clients. This fiduciary duty is a fundamental principle of our firm
        and guides all of our actions and recommendations.
      </p>

      <h3>No Guarantee of Results</h3>
      <p>
        Past performance is not indicative of future results. All investing involves risk,
        including the possible loss of principal. No investment strategy or risk management
        technique can guarantee returns or eliminate risk in any market environment. Diversification
        does not guarantee profit or protect against loss.
      </p>

      <h3>Not Tax or Legal Advice</h3>
      <p>
        Canyon Strategic Wealth does not provide tax or legal advice. The information provided on
        this website and in our advisory services is for general informational and educational
        purposes. We encourage clients to consult with their tax professional and/or attorney for
        specific tax and legal guidance.
      </p>

      <h3>Third-Party Custodian</h3>
      <p>
        Client assets are held by Charles Schwab &amp; Co., Inc., a qualified custodian. Canyon
        Strategic Wealth does not take custody of client funds or securities. Schwab provides
        account statements directly to clients on at least a quarterly basis. Clients should compare
        the information on their custodial statements to reports provided by Canyon Strategic
        Wealth.
      </p>

      <h3>Form ADV</h3>
      <p>
        A copy of our Form ADV Part 2A (Firm Brochure) and Part 2B (Brochure Supplement) is
        available upon request and is filed with the SEC. These documents provide detailed
        information about our qualifications, business practices, and fees. To request a copy,
        please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:jake@canyonstrategicwealth.com">jake@canyonstrategicwealth.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Testimonials &amp; Endorsements</h3>
      <p>
        When client testimonials and endorsements are presented on this website, they may not
        represent the experience of all clients and are not indicative of future performance or
        success. Any testimonials would be provided voluntarily and without compensation.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top:40px;font-size:12px;color:var(--text-light);">
        Last updated: February 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
